article.description: Monmouth coasts to 66-50 win over Niagara
article.headline: Monmouth coasts to 66-50 win over Niagara
article.linkText: Monmouth coasts to 66-50 win over Niagara
article.story: NIAGARA FALLS, N.Y. -- Justin Robinson scored 14 points, including all eight of his shots from the free throw line, to help Monmouth remain unbeaten in Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference games this season with a 66-50 win over Niagara on Sunday. Collin Stewart added 12 points and Deon Jones had eight points while also grabbing seven rebounds for Monmouth (7-7, 4-0), which shot 48 percent from the floor to win its third straight over Niagara (3-9, 2-2). A pair of free throws from Robinson gave Monmouth the lead for good late in the first half and sparked an 11-0 run stretching across both sides of the intermission to make it 33-23 with 18:26 to play. Niagara pulled to within 45-40 on Wesley Myers' layup with 9:03 left but the Hawks responded with a 7-0 burst and continued to pull away down the stretch. Dominique Reid led Niagara with 18 points and 11 rebounds.
